tral along with the Yetti.  Yet again, the break mez first and are off to leave us looking dumb again.<br><br>round 3<br>  We decide to fight fire with fire and get a healer into our group.*at this time I am playing both healer and skald... wifes 43 skald now and my healer*  We spend about 5 to 10 mins looking for team Alb again.  When we find him and attack the minstral again, I have stopped back from the group and go to target the cleric for mez.  As I mez the cleric he had used his PBAOE mez to get the group yet again as I get the cleric and minstral in my AoE mez... great, now we all look like fools standing around with ZZZZ's over us all.  Problem was this.. my AoE mez does not last as long as his and they were off yet again never to be seen again that morning.<br><br>Count is this, 3 attacks, no deaths and 3 escapes for team Alb.  <br><br>  That just sucks.  We all can not figure out how you could possibly fight against that and soon on patch 1.53 I belive, the Hibbies Bards are going to get insta mez and stuns.  UGGGG... what can we do?<br><br>befuddled lvl 43 Skald <p>Rodog<br><br>*fast as fast can be... unless I see a burger joint, then you can find me there*</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/uranolin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ranolin</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/image/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#ff0000>(6/14/02 6:07:55 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=190.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How do you battle this?</span><hr size=1> 1st, I usually mes the cleric and kill the minstrel.  Minstrels go down easy and are often bots that give no resistance, then the slow cleric may be hunted at leisure.<br><br>2nd, I have purge, and no cleric pbaoe would allow him to escape that easily.<br><br><br>3rd, if you knew the cleric was going to PBAE mes, then you could have come at him one at a time.  Basically you(the skald) should hang back, let the warriors get in there, get mezzed, and then you get on top of the cleric with shouts and kick his arse.<br><br>Happy hunting<br>Ranolin <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#efe0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/ueregil.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Eregil</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://users.iol.it/okandrea/Eregil.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Contributor</span><br>  Posts: 28<br> <font color=#ff0000>(6/14/02 6:47:21 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=190.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://users.iol.it/okandrea/ereliz.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How do you battle this?</span><hr size=1> Yea what he said.... <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br><br>From what you describe I assume none of you had purge, therefore the only way to beat them is run in 2 waves. You have speed and mez so you need to be last to go in unless, you can attack them by surprise.<br><br>Let the first wave be insta mezzed and the second come in and rip the cleric to shreads. His stun is a cast, so once you start beeting on him no more stuns/mezzes. Remember to mez the Minstrel and have the trolls prepare for dinner after. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :smokin --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smokin.gif ALT=":smokin"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><IMG BORDER="0" SRC="http://users.iol.it/okandrea/EreNi.gif"></CENTER></p><i>Edited by